abstract: AT&T moved on Friday to dismiss antitrust lawsuits by Sprint Nextel and Cellular South, arguing that both companies were looking to block the deal for self-interested reasons.
snippet: AT&T moved on Friday to dismiss antitrust lawsuits by Sprint Nextel and Cellular South, arguing that both companies were looking to block the deal for self-interested reasons.
lead_paragraph: The legal fusillades have continued in the battle over AT&T‘s proposed $39 billion acquisition of T-Mobile USA, as the company sought on Friday to take shots at competitors seeking to stop the takeover.

headline.main: AT&T Moves to Dismiss Lawsuits by Sprint and Cellular South

byline.original: By Michael J. de la Merced
